article.description: Johanna Solverson scored 19 points and converted a key three-point play in the closing minute to secure Iowa's 76-69 victory Tuesday night over Western Illinois.
article.headline: Solverson scores 19 for Iowa
article.linkText: Hawkeyes blow lead but beat Western Illinois
article.story:
IOWA CITY, Iowa (AP) -- Johanna Solverson scored 19 points and converted a key three-point play in the closing minute to secure Iowa's 76-69 victory Tuesday night over Western Illinois.

Solverson fought for an offensive rebound over two Westerwinds, somehow muscled up a shot and hit the free throw to extend the Iowa lead to seven points with 1:14 left. Iowa (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) made 6-of-7 free-throw attempts in the final two minutes, hitting a season-best 86 percent for the game.

Crystal Smith added 18 points and Jamie Cavey 15 points and nine rebounds for the Hawkeyes (10-0). Jessica Cook scored 16 of her 22 points in the second half for Western Illinois (4-5), and Zane Teilane had 20 points, eight rebounds and blocked seven shots.

Rita Castans added 14 points for Western Illinois.

Smith scorched the Hawkeyes on 7-of-9 shooting after the break. The aggressive guard made jump shots from every angle on the court, sinking turnarounds and fadeaways.

Iowa was flustered by Western Illinois' matchup defense in the second half, slowing penetration and forcing outside jumpers.

A once-comfortable lead slipped away, sinking to four points four times in the last nine minutes.
